- 'sale_rank = 1' refers to the most recent sale for each model;
- 'total_revenue > (SELECT AVG(total_revenue) FROM sales)' means the revenue from the sale is greater than the average revenue of all sales.

- 'Total sales revenue' is the sum of revenue from all sales of a particular equipment model;
- 'Average fuel consumption' is the mean fuel consumption rate for a given equipment model;
- 'Most recent maintenance type' refers to the type of the latest maintenance performed on the equipment model;
- 'Emergency' maintenance is typically urgent and unplanned.

- "Significant sales and revenue" refers to models with total sales greater than 10 and total revenue greater than 100,000;
- "Performance metrics" include average noise level and average fuel consumption;
- "Maintenance costs" refer to the average maintenance cost for each model.

